    "path": "about/use-cases-73626998.html",
    "text": "Mianotes is useful whenever humans and agents need a shared, searchable, local knowledge base. Developers using AI agents Use Mianotes as the documentation layer for Codex, Claude Code, Cursor, OpenClaw, VS Code agents, Slack bots, and local automation. Every local agent has a goal, and every agent needs a place to report back. Mianotes gives agents a local workspace where they can explain what they did, how they did it, what changed, and what the outcome was. Agents can save: Task summaries Implementation notes Decisions and trade offs Changed files and why they changed Debugging findings Test results Questions and proposals Project context for the next agent run This gives the person orchestrating the work a clear record of what happened: what their agents are doing, how they are doing it, and the result of each task. All of that context is captured and centralised in one place. AI agents and tools Agents can use Mianotes as long term memory that stays under your control. An agent can: Create a folder for a task Add notes as it works Convert source files to Markdown Tag notes for discovery Search earlier notes before making changes Update a note when new evidence arrives Leave comments for review or handoff Students Students can use Mianotes to turn study material into clean, searchable notes. Upload lecture slides, book pages, whiteboards, images, handwritten notes, or audio recordings, then ask Mia to structure the material as Markdown. Biology revision History essays Maths examples Lecture notes Useful Mia prompts include: Small teams Small teams can use Mianotes as a shared local knowledge base. Typical folders: Spec and PRD files Research Meeting notes Internal decisions Roadmaps Launch plans Team members can add tags across folders, comment on notes, and create read only share links when someone outside the workspace needs access to a single note. Researchers Researchers can use Mianotes to keep links, papers, documents, notes, prompts, and summaries in one searchable place. Mianotes is especially useful when source material is messy because URL and file ingestion can preserve the original source next to the generated Markdown note. Families and everyday use Mianotes also works as a private home knowledge base. Examples: Homework School documents Trip plans Medical appointment notes Images of forms or letters The value is not only AI. The value is that the final note is readable text, stored locally, and easy to search."
