    "text": "This page documents authentication, session, token, and user endpoints. Check email Authentication: none. Request: First user setup response: Existing user response: Join Authentication: none. If no Mianotes workspace has been initialized, this endpoint creates the first admin user and stores the master password. Request: The response sets an HTTP only mianotes session cookie. Login Authentication: none. Request: The response sets an HTTP only mianotes session cookie. Get current session Authentication: session cookie or bearer token. Example: Create agent session Authentication: bearer API key or scoped API token. Required headers: Mianotes validates the bearer token, maps X Mianotes Client into a stable client ID, signs that identity into a short lived session token, and returns the token for follow up requests. Unknown client names default to MCP . The raw API key is not embedded in the session token. Response: Logout Authentication: none. Response: 204 No Content . Create scoped API token Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with tokens\\:write or admin . Request: The raw token is returned only once. List API tokens Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with tokens\\:read or admin . Query parameters: | Parameter | Description | | | | | user id | Optional user whose tokens should be listed. Admin only for other users. | | include revoked | Include revoked tokens. Defaults to false . | Raw token values are not returned by this endpoint. Revoke API token Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with tokens\\:write or admin . Response: 204 No Content . Create service API key Authentication: admin session or bearer token with admin . Creates the service wide key used by local agents and MCP clients. The service writes the raw key to its environment file and stores only a public verifier in the active database. Response: The raw key is returned only once. User endpoints | Method | Path | Purpose | Auth | | | | | | | POST | /api/users | Create a user directly | Admin | | GET | /api/users | List users | users\\:read or admin | | GET | /api/users/{user id} | Get one user | users\\:read or admin | | PATCH | /api/users/{user id} | Update profile | profile owner or admin | | POST | /api/users/{user id}/photo | Upload profile photo | profile owner or admin | | DELETE | /api/users/{user id} | Delete user | Admin | Profile photos accept JPG or PNG files, crop and resize to 200x200 , convert to JPEG, and store the resized image under data/.profiles ."
