    "text": "This page documents the core knowledge endpoints. Folder object Create folder Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with folders\\:write or admin . Request: The folder owner is always the current user. List folders Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with folders\\:read or admin . Query parameters: | Parameter | Description | | | | | user id | Return folders created by a specific user. | | include archived | Include archived folders. Defaults to false . | Update folder Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with folders\\:write or admin . Admins can update any folder. Normal users can update only folders they created. Archive folder Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with folders\\:write or admin . Archived folders are hidden unless include archived=true . Restore folder Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with folders\\:write or admin . Admins can restore any archived folder. Normal users can restore only folders they created. Request: Both fields are optional. If the original folder slug is already taken, Mianotes creates a unique restored slug. Create note from text Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:write or admin . Request: Tags are limited to 5 per note. Create note from file Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:write or admin . Request: multipart/form data . | Field | Required | Description | | | :| | | folder id | Yes | Folder ID for the note. | | file | Yes | Source file to upload. | | title | Yes | Note title. | The response returns a pending note plus a queued parse file job. Clients should poll job api url , then fetch note api url after success. Supported upload extensions: Create note from URL Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:write or admin . Request: The response returns a pending note plus a queued parse url job. List notes Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:read or admin . Query parameters: | Parameter | Description | | | | | user id | Return notes created by a specific user. | | folder id | Return notes in a specific folder. | | starred | Return notes starred or not starred by the authenticated user. | List responses include metadata and a stored summary, but not full Markdown text. Get note Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:read or admin . Returns a full note including Markdown text , owner, folder, source files, tags, comment metadata, sharing metadata, and action hints. Update note Authentication: session cookie or bearer token with notes\\:write or admin . Request fields: Admins can update any note. Normal users can update only notes they created. Star note Stars are private per user. Request: Delete note Deletes the note, stored Markdown file, source files, and related comments. Tags List global tags: Replace a note's tag set: Request:"
